{
  "texts": [
    "Table III shows the results when the model is fine-tuned on the train-clean-100 subset.",
    "Obviously, when we only use the codes derived from GAN for pre-training, our T-HuBERT (5.0/11.2%) outperforms HuBERT (6.3/13.2%) with a large margin, and yields comparable results with token2vec (5.1/11.8%).",
    "It suggests the effectiveness of our proposed GAN-based tokenizer that can effectively leverage additional unpaired text in an unsupervised way to provide better targets for speech pre-training.2) The choice of supervision layer for the GAN-based pseudo codes: Here we study the effect of layer choices for the GAN-based pseudo codes.",
    "The HuBERT-based codes are always put at the 12th layer of the model, and we only vary the position of the GAN-based codes.",
    "Due to limited resources, we conduct experiments using smaller models with embedding size 384, 6 attention heads, and feed-forward dimension 1536 in each transformer block."
  ]
}